OL,6,FShe was jailed for a further six
OL,7,Fmonths for unrelated offences
OL,8,Fincluding shoplifting and drug
OL,9,Fpossession charges.
OL,11,FMary Cowe, prosecuting, told the court
OL,12,FMr Shadwick was "extremely vulnerable"
OL,13,Fand lived in supported accommodation
OL,14,Fin Stroud, relying on carers visiting
OL,15,Fhim four times a day.
OL,17,F"This defendant was known to have come
OL,18,Fto his home and was a regular visitor
OL,19,Ffrom the end of 2021," she said.
