OL,3,CWoman stole man's mobility scooter and
OL,4,Cleft him to die in -6C temperatures
OL,6,F"This was a man who was physically
OL,7,Fvulnerable and that would have been
OL,8,Fobvious to anyone who visited."
OL,10,FDescribing the incident that led to
OL,11,Fhis death, Miss Cowe said: "There
OL,12,Fcomes a point where he has stepped off
OL,13,Fthe scooter and uses it steady himself.
OL,15,F"The defendant climbs in and drives
OL,16,Foff. Hawkins drove the scooter for 57
OL,17,Fseconds, dragging Mr Shadwick along
OL,18,Fthe road.
